116// Values from the instance object are cached between Wasm-level function calls.
117// This struct allows the SSA environment handling this cache to be defined
118// and manipulated in wasm-compiler.{h,cc} instead of inside the Wasm decoder.
119// (Note that currently, the globals base is immutable, so not cached here.)
120struct WasmInstanceCacheNodes {
121 // Cache the memory start and size of one fixed memory per function. Which one
122 // is determined by {WasmGraphBuilder::cached_memory_index}.
123 Node* mem_start = nullptr;
124 Node* mem_size = nullptr;
125
126 // For iteration support. Defined outside the class for MSVC compatibility.
127 using FieldPtr = Node* WasmInstanceCacheNodes::*;
128 static const FieldPtr kFields[2];
129};
130inline constexpr WasmInstanceCacheNodes::FieldPtr
131 WasmInstanceCacheNodes::kFields[] = {&WasmInstanceCacheNodes::mem_start,
132 &WasmInstanceCacheNodes::mem_size};
133
134struct WasmLoopInfo {
135 Node* header;
136 uint32_t nesting_depth;
137 // This loop has, to our best knowledge, no other loops nested within it. A
138 // loop can obtain inner loops despite this after inlining.
139 bool can_be_innermost;
140
141 WasmLoopInfo(Node* header, uint32_t nesting_depth, bool can_be_innermost)
142 : header(header),
143 nesting_depth(nesting_depth),
144 can_be_innermost(can_be_innermost) {}
145};
146
147struct WasmCompilationData {
148 explicit WasmCompilationData(const wasm::FunctionBody& func_body)
149 : func_body(func_body) {}
150
151 size_t body_size() { return func_body.end - func_body.start; }
152
153 const wasm::FunctionBody& func_body;
154 const wasm::WireBytesStorage* wire_bytes_storage;
155 NodeOriginTable* node_origins{nullptr};
156 std::vector<WasmLoopInfo>* loop_infos{nullptr};
157 wasm::AssumptionsJournal* assumptions{nullptr};
158 SourcePositionTable* source_positions{nullptr};
159 int func_index;
160};

162// Abstracts details of building TurboFan graph nodes for wasm to separate
163// the wasm decoder from the internal details of TurboFan.
164class WasmGraphBuilder {
165 public:
166 // ParameterMode specifies how the instance is passed.
167 enum ParameterMode {
168 // Normal wasm functions pass the instance as an implicit first parameter.
169 kInstanceParameterMode,
170 // For Wasm-to-JS and C-API wrappers, a {WasmApiFunctionRef} object is
171 // passed as first parameter.
172 kWasmApiFunctionRefMode,
173 // For JS-to-Wasm wrappers (which are JS functions), we load the Wasm
174 // instance from the JS function data. The generated code objects live on
175 // the JS heap, so those compilation pass an isolate.
176 kJSFunctionAbiMode,
177 // The JS-to-JS wrapper does not have an associated instance.
178 // The C-entry stub uses a custom ABI (see {CWasmEntryParameters}).
179 kNoSpecialParameterMode
180 };
181
182 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE WasmGraphBuilder(wasm::CompilationEnv* env, Zone* zone,
183 MachineGraph* mcgraph,
184 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
185 compiler::SourcePositionTable* spt,
186 ParameterMode parameter_mode,
187 Isolate* isolate,
188 wasm::WasmFeatures enabled_features);
189
190 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE ~WasmGraphBuilder();
